 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.436","title":"[audit][grpc] Accept case-insensitive Bearer auth scheme in interceptor validator","description":"Follow-up defect in src/grpc/interceptor.rs: BearerAuthValidator currently only accepts an exact `Bearer ` prefix even though HTTP auth-schemes are case-insensitive. Patch the validator to accept case-insensitive bearer scheme matching without loosening token parsing, add focused regression tests, validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands, and append an audit_index entry when complete.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"TopazHeron","created_at":"2026-03-25T23:12:59.437494009Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T23:25:16.322998617Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T23:25:16.322644820Z","close_reason":"Current HEAD already contains the case-insensitive bearer-scheme validator follow-up and its regressions; no unique code diff remains from this slice. Validated current head with rch-backed cargo check -p asupersync --lib and cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib -- -D warnings.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.436","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-25T23:12:59.437494009Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
