 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.44","title":"[audit][web] Give TimeoutMiddleware a deterministic time getter","description":"TimeoutMiddleware in src/web/middleware.rs still measures elapsed time with std::time::Instant::now(), which makes its behavior hard-wired to wall-clock timing even though adjacent web middleware already exposes custom time getters for deterministic tests. Add a custom time_getter path for TimeoutMiddleware, thread it through the middleware implementation, add focused regression coverage that proves timeout behavior can be driven without sleeping, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"SilentEagle","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T05:01:09.071356332Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:37.036765874Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:37.036765874Z","close_reason":"Completed: added TimeoutMiddleware::with_time_getter plus deterministic regression tests; full all-target validation blocked by unrelated src/http/h1/codec.rs test compile error and merge markers in asupersync-tokio-compat/src/runtime.rs","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:37.036734736Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","determinism","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.44","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T05:01:09.071356332Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.45","title":"[audit][web][session] Expire unknown fixation cookies on read-only requests","description":"SessionMiddleware currently treats unknown-but-valid session IDs as fixation attempts, but for read-only requests it leaves the attacker-supplied cookie in place because no new session is persisted and no cookie expiration is emitted. Patch src/web/session.rs so unknown valid IDs are actively expired even when the handler does not mutate session state, add focused regression coverage, and validate with rch-backed targeted cargo check/clippy/test commands.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"BrightMill","estimated_minutes":45,"created_at":"2026-03-09T05:02:54.940225743Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:25.377119764Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:25.377119764Z","close_reason":"Fixed unknown fixation cookie expiry in SessionMiddleware; added read-only regression coverage. Validation: rch remote targeted test passed; rch remote cargo check -p asupersync --lib exposed pre-existing unresolved memmem import in src/http/h1/codec.rs; rch remote cargo clippy -p asupersync --lib passed; workspace cargo fmt --check is blocked by existing merge conflict markers in asupersync-tokio-compat/src/runtime.rs; rustfmt --check src/web/session.rs passed.","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:25.377072737Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","security","session","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.45","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T05:02:54.940225743Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-1qfd0.46","title":"[audit][web] Make standalone compress/security middleware respect case-insensitive public headers","description":"src/web/compress.rs and src/web/security.rs assume lowercase keys in public Request/Response header HashMaps, so mixed-case headers inserted directly through the public fields can bypass Accept-Encoding negotiation, duplicate security headers, or leave Server unstripped. Fix the standalone web modules to use case-insensitive header access/canonicalization, add focused regressions, and validate with rch-backed fmt/check/clippy/test commands on the touched surface.","status":"tombstone","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"CoralCompass","created_at":"2026-03-09T05:07:31.575656032Z","created_by":"EmeraldRiver","updated_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:27.263125980Z","closed_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:27.263125980Z","close_reason":"Current tree already satisfies bead contract; case-insensitive header handling and regressions are already present","source_repo":".","deleted_at":"2026-03-23T07:08:27.263105151Z","deleted_by":"system","delete_reason":"merge deletion","original_type":"bug","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["audit","headers","web"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.46","depends_on_id":"asupersync-1qfd0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-09T05:07:31.575656032Z","created_by":"EmeraldRiver","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2475,"issue_id":"asupersync-1qfd0.46","author":"CoralCompass","text":"Audit result: current tree already satisfies this bead.

Source evidence:
- Request-side lookup is already case-insensitive in `src/web/extract.rs:89` (`Request::header`) so direct mixed-case `Accept-Encoding` inserts are honored by `src/web/compress.rs:110`.
- Response-side helpers already canonicalize and match case-insensitively in `src/web/response.rs:154` (`header_value`), `src/web/response.rs:173` (`set_header`), `src/web/response.rs:190` (`ensure_header`), and `src/web/response.rs:200` (`remove_header`).
- Compression regressions already cover the mixed-case cases at `src/web/compress.rs:293`, `src/web/compress.rs:310`, and `src/web/compress.rs:328`.
- Security-header regressions already cover the mixed-case cases at `src/web/security.rs:267` and `src/web/security.rs:344`.
- Supporting response helper regressions exist at `src/web/response.rs:478` and `src/web/response.rs:490`.
- File-local formatting check passed: `rustfmt --edition 2024 --check src/web/compress.rs src/web/security.rs src/web/response.rs src/web/extract.rs`.

Conclusion: no code change required for this bead; the requested case-insensitive behavior and canonicalization regressions are already present.","created_at":"2026-03-10T05:45:02Z"}]}
